#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:604
msgid "Label Matching"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:606
msgid ""
"Tests may have labels attached to them. Tests may be included or excluded "
"from a test run by filtering on the labels. Each individual filter is a "
"regular expression applied to the labels attached to a test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:611
msgid ""
"When :ctest-option:`-L` is used, in order for a test to be included in a "
"test run, each regular expression must match at least one label.  Using more "
"than one :ctest-option:`-L` option means \"match **all** of these\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:615
msgid ""
"The :ctest-option:`-LE` option works just like :ctest-option:`-L`, but "
"excludes tests rather than including them. A test is excluded if each "
"regular expression matches at least one label."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:619
msgid ""
"If a test has no labels attached to it, then :ctest-option:`-L` will never "
"include that test, and :ctest-option:`-LE` will never exclude that test. As "
"an example of tests with labels, consider five tests, with the following "
"labels:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:624
msgid "*test1* has labels *tuesday* and *production*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:625
msgid "*test2* has labels *tuesday* and *test*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:626
msgid "*test3* has labels *wednesday* and *production*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:627
msgid "*test4* has label *wednesday*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:628
msgid "*test5* has labels *friday* and *test*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:630
msgid ""
"Running :program:`ctest` with ``-L tuesday -L test`` will select *test2*, "
"which has both labels. Running CTest with ``-L test`` will select *test2* "
"and *test5*, because both of them have a label that matches that regular "
"expression."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:635
msgid ""
"Because the matching works with regular expressions, take note that running "
"CTest with ``-L es`` will match all five tests. To select the *tuesday* and "
"*wednesday* tests together, use a single regular expression that matches "
"either of them, like ``-L \"tue|wed\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:643
msgid "Label and Subproject Summary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:645
msgid ""
"CTest prints timing summary information for each ``LABEL`` and subproject "
"associated with the tests run. The label time summary will not include "
"labels that are mapped to subprojects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:649
msgid ""
"Labels added dynamically during test execution are also reported in the "
"timing summary.  See :ref:`Additional Labels`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:653
msgid ""
"When the :prop_test:`PROCESSORS` test property is set, CTest will display a "
"weighted test timing result in label and subproject summaries. The time is "
"reported with ``sec * proc`` instead of just ``sec``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:657
msgid ""
"The weighted time summary reported for each label or subproject ``j`` is "
"computed as::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:660
msgid ""
"Weighted Time Summary for Label/Subproject j =\n"
"    sum(raw_test_time[j,i] * num_processors[j,i], i=1...num_tests[j])\n"
"\n"
"for labels/subprojects j=1...total"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:665
msgid "where:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:667
msgid ""
"``raw_test_time[j,i]``: Wall-clock time for the ``i`` test for the ``j`` "
"label or subproject"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:669
msgid ""
"``num_processors[j,i]``: Value of the CTest :prop_test:`PROCESSORS` property "
"for the ``i`` test for the ``j`` label or subproject"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:671
msgid ""
"``num_tests[j]``: Number of tests associated with the ``j`` label or "
"subproject"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:672
msgid ""
"``total``: Total number of labels or subprojects that have at least one test "
"run"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:674
msgid ""
"Therefore, the weighted time summary for each label or subproject represents "
"the amount of time that CTest gave to run the tests for each label or "
"subproject and gives a good representation of the total expense of the tests "
"for each label or subproject when compared to other labels or subprojects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:679
msgid ""
"For example, if ``SubprojectA`` showed ``100 sec*proc`` and ``SubprojectB`` "
"showed ``10 sec*proc``, then CTest allocated approximately 10 times the CPU/"
"core time to run the tests for ``SubprojectA`` than for ``SubprojectB`` (e."
"g. so if effort is going to be expended to reduce the cost of the test suite "
"for the whole project, then reducing the cost of the test suite for "
"``SubprojectA`` would likely have a larger impact than effort to reduce the "
"cost of the test suite for ``SubprojectB``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:690
msgid "Build and Test Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:692
msgid ""
"CTest provides a command-line signature to configure (i.e. run cmake on), "
"build, and/or execute a test::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:695
msgid ""
"ctest --build-and-test <path-to-source> <path-to-build>\n"
"      --build-generator <generator>\n"
"      [<options>...]\n"
"      [--build-options <opts>...]\n"
"      [--test-command <command> [<args>...]]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:701
msgid ""
"The configure and test steps are optional. The arguments to this command "
"line are the source and binary directories.  The ``--build-generator`` "
"option *must* be provided to use ``--build-and-test``.  If ``--test-"
"command`` is specified then that will be run after the build is complete.  "
"Other options that affect this mode include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:709
msgid "Switch into the build and test mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:713
msgid ""
"Specify a specific target to build.  The option can be given multiple times "
"with different targets, in which case each target is built in turn. A clean "
"will be done before building each target unless the :option:`--build-"
"noclean` option is given."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:718
msgid "If no ``--build-target`` is specified, the ``all`` target is built."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:722
msgid "Run the build without running :program:`cmake` first."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:724
msgid "Skip the :program:`cmake` step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:728
msgid "Specify directory to run programs from."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:730
msgid "Directory where programs will be after it has been compiled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:734
msgid "Run CMake twice."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:738
msgid "Specify the directory for the executable."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:742
msgid ""
"Specify the generator to use. See the :manual:`cmake-generators(7)` manual."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:746
msgid "Specify the generator-specific platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:750
msgid "Specify the generator-specific toolset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:754
msgid "Specify the name of the project to build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:758
msgid ""
"Specify the explicit make program to be used by CMake when configuring and "
"building the project. Only applicable for :ref:`Makefile Generators` and :"
"ref:`Ninja Generators`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:764
msgid "Skip the make clean step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:768
msgid ""
"A sample executable to use to determine the configuration that should be "
"used (e.g.  ``Debug``, ``Release``, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:773
msgid ""
"Additional options for configuring the build (i.e. for :manual:`cmake(1)`, "
"not for the build tool).  Note that if this is specified, the ``--build-"
"options`` keyword and its arguments must be the last option given on the "
"command line, with the possible exception of :ctest-option:`--test-command`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:781
msgid ""
"The command to run as the test step with the :ctest-option:`--build-and-"
"test` option. All arguments following this keyword will be assumed to be "
"part of the test command line, so it must be the last option given."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:788
msgid "The time limit in seconds."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:793
msgid "Dashboard Client"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:795
msgid ""
"CTest can operate as a client for the `CDash`_ software quality dashboard "
"application.  As a dashboard client, CTest performs a sequence of steps to "
"configure, build, and test software, and then submits the results to a "
"`CDash`_ server. The command-line signature used to submit to `CDash`_ is::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:800
msgid ""
"ctest -D <dashboard>         [-- <dashboard-options>...]\n"
"ctest -M <model> -T <action> [-- <dashboard-options>...]\n"
"ctest -S <script>            [-- <dashboard-options>...]\n"
"ctest -SP <script>           [-- <dashboard-options>...]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:807
msgid "Options for Dashboard Client include:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:811
msgid "Execute dashboard test."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:813
msgid ""
"This option tells CTest to act as a CDash client and perform a dashboard "
"test.  All tests are ``<Mode><Test>``, where ``<Mode>`` can be "
"``Experimental``, ``Nightly``, and ``Continuous``, and ``<Test>`` can be "
"``Start``, ``Update``, ``Configure``, ``Build``, ``Test``, ``Coverage``, and "
"``Submit``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:819
msgid ""
"If ``<dashboard>`` is not one of the recognized ``<Mode><Test>`` values, "
"this will be treated as a variable definition instead (see the :ref:"
"`dashboard-options <Dashboard Options>` further below)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:825
msgid "Sets the model for a dashboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:827
msgid ""
"This option tells CTest to act as a CDash client where the ``<model>`` can "
"be ``Experimental``, ``Nightly``, and ``Continuous``. Combining ``-M`` and :"
"ctest-option:`-T` is similar to :ctest-option:`-D`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:833
msgid "Sets the dashboard action to perform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:835
msgid ""
"This option tells CTest to act as a CDash client and perform some action "
"such as ``start``, ``build``, ``test`` etc. See `Dashboard Client Steps`_ "
"for the full list of actions. Combining :ctest-option:`-M` and ``-T`` is "
"similar to :ctest-option:`-D`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:842 ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:852
msgid "Execute a dashboard for a configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:844
msgid ""
"This option tells CTest to load in a configuration script which sets a "
"number of parameters such as the binary and source directories. Then CTest "
"will do what is required to create and run a dashboard. This option "
"basically sets up a dashboard and then runs :option:`ctest -D` with the "
"appropriate options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:854
msgid ""
"This option does the same operations as :ctest-option:`-S` but it will do "
"them in a separate process.  This is primarily useful in cases where the "
"script may modify the environment and you do not want the modified "
"environment to impact other :ctest-option:`-S` scripts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:861
msgid "The available ``<dashboard-options>`` are the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:867
msgid "Define a variable for dashboard client mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:869
msgid ""
"Pass in variable values on the command line.  Use in conjunction with :ctest-"
"option:`-S` to pass variable values to a dashboard script, or with :ctest-"
"option:`-T` to override `Dashboard Client Configuration`_ settings. Parsing "
"``-D`` arguments as variable values is only attempted if the value following "
"``-D`` does not match any of the known dashboard types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:875
msgid ""
"The ``<var>:<type>=<value>`` form accepts any variable name.  The simpler "
"``<var>=<value>`` form (without a type) is accepted only for variables whose "
"names begin with ``CTEST_``.  In both cases the value overrides the "
"corresponding setting from the `Dashboard Client Configuration`_ file (e.g., "
"``DartConfiguration.tcl``) when using :ctest-option:`-T`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:882
msgid ""
"These definitions set CTest script variables (e.g., :variable:"
"`CTEST_BUILD_NAME`), not CMake cache variables. To pass CMake cache "
"variables to the configure step, consider using a `CTest Script`_, a :manual:"
"`configure preset <cmake-presets(7)>`, or setting :variable:"
"`CTEST_CONFIGURE_COMMAND`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:892
msgid ""
"Specify the project source directory. When combined with :option:`-T "
"Configure <ctest -T>`, this allows CTest to perform an initial configure "
"step for an empty binary directory.  The binary directory defaults to the "
"current working directory; use :ctest-dashboard-option:`--build-dir` to "
"specify a different location. The binary directory is created automatically "
"if it does not yet exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:899
msgid ""
"When a :manual:`configure preset <cmake-presets(7)>` is specified that "
"defines a :preset:`binaryDir <configurePresets.binaryDir>`, CTest uses that "
"path as the binary directory automatically (without requiring :ctest-"
"dashboard-option:`--build-dir`).  An explicit :ctest-dashboard-option:`--"
"build-dir` takes precedence over the preset's :preset:`binaryDir "
"<configurePresets.binaryDir>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:906
msgid ""
"A CMake generator must also be specified. Use :option:`-D "
"CTEST_CMAKE_GENERATOR=\\<gen\\> <ctest-dashboard -D>` to supply one, or set :"
"variable:`CTEST_CONFIGURE_PRESET` to specify a :manual:`configure preset "
"<cmake-presets(7)>` that includes a :preset:`generator <configurePresets."
"generator>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:912
msgid "See the `CTest Configure Step`_ settings for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:918
msgid ""
"Specify the project binary (build) directory. This is an alias for :ctest-"
"option:`--test-dir` intended for use with :ctest-dashboard-option:`--source-"
"dir` when bootstrapping a build with :option:`-T Configure <ctest -T>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:925
msgid "Specify the group to which to submit results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:927
msgid ""
"Submit dashboard to specified group instead of the default.  By default, the "
"dashboard is submitted to Nightly, Experimental, or Continuous group, but by "
"specifying this option, the group can be arbitrary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:932
msgid ""
"This replaces the deprecated option ``--track``. Despite the name change its "
"behavior is unchanged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:937
msgid "Add a notes file with submission."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:939
msgid ""
"This option tells CTest to include a notes file when submitting dashboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:944
msgid "``Nightly`` or ``Experimental`` starts with next day tag."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:946
msgid "This is useful if the build will not finish in one day."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:950
msgid ""
"Submit extra ``.xml`` part files to the dashboard. See the :command:"
"`ctest_submit` command's ``PARTS ExtraFiles`` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:957
msgid "Append HTTP header when submitting to the dashboard."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:959
msgid ""
"This option will cause CTest to append the specified header when submitting "
"to the dashboard. This option may be specified more than once."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:965
msgid "Submit using ``HTTP 1.0``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:967
msgid ""
"This option will force CTest to use ``HTTP 1.0`` to submit files to the "
"dashboard, instead of ``HTTP 1.1``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:972
msgid "Do not compress test output when submitting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:974
msgid ""
"This flag will turn off automatic compression of test output.  Use this to "
"maintain compatibility with an older version of CDash which doesn't support "
"compressed test output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:979
msgid "Dashboard Client Steps"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:981
msgid ""
"CTest defines an ordered list of testing steps of which some or all may be "
"run as a dashboard client:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:984
msgid "``Start``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:985
msgid ""
"Start a new dashboard submission to be composed of results recorded by the "
"following steps. See the `CTest Start Step`_ section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:989
msgid "``Update``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:990
msgid ""
"Update the source tree from its version control repository. Record the old "
"and new versions and the list of updated source files. See the `CTest Update "
"Step`_ section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:994
msgid "``Configure``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:995
msgid ""
"Configure the software by running a command in the build tree. Record the "
"configuration output log. See the `CTest Configure Step`_ section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:999
msgid "``Build``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1000
msgid ""
"Build the software by running a command in the build tree. Record the build "
"output log and detect warnings and errors. See the `CTest Build Step`_ "
"section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1004
msgid "``Test``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1005
msgid ""
"Test the software by loading a ``CTestTestfile.cmake`` from the build tree "
"and executing the defined tests. Record the output and result of each test. "
"See the `CTest Test Step`_ section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1010
msgid "``Coverage``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1011
msgid ""
"Compute coverage of the source code by running a coverage analysis tool and "
"recording its output. See the `CTest Coverage Step`_ section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1015
msgid "``MemCheck``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1016
msgid ""
"Run the software test suite through a memory check tool. Record the test "
"output, results, and issues reported by the tool. See the `CTest MemCheck "
"Step`_ section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1020
msgid "``Submit``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1021
msgid ""
"Submit results recorded from other testing steps to the software quality "
"dashboard server. See the `CTest Submit Step`_ section below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1026
msgid "Dashboard Client Modes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1028
msgid "CTest defines three modes of operation as a dashboard client:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1030
msgid "``Nightly``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1031
msgid ""
"This mode is intended to be invoked once per day, typically at night. It "
"enables the ``Start``, ``Update``, ``Configure``, ``Build``, ``Test``, "
"``Coverage``, and ``Submit`` steps by default.  Selected steps run even if "
"the ``Update`` step reports no changes to the source tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1036
msgid "``Continuous``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1037
msgid ""
"This mode is intended to be invoked repeatedly throughout the day. It "
"enables the ``Start``, ``Update``, ``Configure``, ``Build``, ``Test``, "
"``Coverage``, and ``Submit`` steps by default, but exits after the "
"``Update`` step if it reports no changes to the source tree."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1042
msgid "``Experimental``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1043
msgid ""
"This mode is intended to be invoked by a developer to test local changes. It "
"enables the ``Start``, ``Configure``, ``Build``, ``Test``, ``Coverage``, and "
"``Submit`` steps by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1048
msgid "Dashboard Client via CTest Command-Line"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1050
msgid ""
"CTest can perform testing on an already-generated build tree. Run the :"
"program:`ctest` command with the current working directory set to the build "
"tree and use one of these signatures::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1054
msgid ""
"ctest -D <mode>[<step>]\n"
"ctest -M <mode> [-T <step>]..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1057
msgid ""
"The :ctest-dashboard-option:`--source-dir` option additionally allows the "
"``Configure`` step to be performed on a build tree that does not yet exist, "
"in which case the :ctest-dashboard-option:`--build-dir` option specifies "
"where to create it::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1062
msgid ""
"ctest [-M <mode>] -T Configure\n"
"    --source-dir <path-to-source> [--build-dir <path-to-build>]\n"
"ctest --build-and-test <path-to-source> <path-to-build>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1066
msgid ""
"The ``<mode>`` must be one of the above `Dashboard Client Modes`_, and each "
"``<step>`` must be one of the above `Dashboard Client Steps`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1069
msgid ""
"CTest reads the `Dashboard Client Configuration`_ settings from a file in "
"the build tree called either ``CTestConfiguration.ini`` or "
"``DartConfiguration.tcl`` (the names are historical).  The format of the "
"file is::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1074
msgid ""
"# Lines starting in '#' are comments.\n"
"# Other non-blank lines are key-value pairs.\n"
"<setting>: <value>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1078
msgid ""
"where ``<setting>`` is the setting name and ``<value>`` is the setting value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1081
msgid ""
"In build trees generated by CMake, this configuration file is generated by "
"the :module:`CTest` module if included by the project. The module uses "
"variables to obtain a value for each setting as documented with the settings "
"below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1089
msgid "Dashboard Client via CTest Script"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1091
msgid ""
"CTest can perform testing driven by a :manual:`cmake-language(7)` script "
"that creates and maintains the source and build tree as well as performing "
"the testing steps.  Run the :program:`ctest` command with the current "
"working directory set outside of any build tree and use one of these "
"signatures::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1097
msgid ""
"ctest -S <script>\n"
"ctest -SP <script>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1100
msgid ""
"The ``<script>`` file must call :ref:`CTest Commands` commands to run "
"testing steps explicitly as documented below.  The commands obtain "
"`Dashboard Client Configuration`_ settings from their arguments or from "
"variables set in the script."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1106
msgid "Dashboard Client Configuration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1108
msgid ""
"The `Dashboard Client Steps`_ may be configured by named settings as "
"documented in the following sections."
msgstr ""

