"Optional field specifying the configuration for which the test will run. "
"This will always match the :ctest-option:`-C` option specified on the :"
"program:`ctest` command line.  If no such option was given, this field will "
"not be present."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1936
msgid ""
"Optional array where the first element is the test command and the remaining "
"elements are the command arguments.  Normally, this field should be present "
"and non-empty, but in certain corner cases involving generator expressions, "
"it is possible for a test to have no command and therefore this field can be "
"missing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1941
msgid "``backtrace``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1942
msgid "Index into the ``nodes`` member of the ``backtraceGraph``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1943
msgid "``properties``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1944
msgid ""
"Optional array of test properties. Each array item will be a JSON object "
"with the following members:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1948
msgid "The name of the test property. This cannot be empty."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1949
msgid "``value``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1950
msgid ""
"The property value, which can be a string, a number, a boolean, or an array "
"of strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../manual/ctest.1.rst:1953
msgid ""
"The JSON output format is described in machine-readable form by :download:"
